==Description== <!--T:8-->

<!--T:2-->
The [[FEM_SolverZ88|SolverZ88]] command enables usage of the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Z88_FEM_software Z88] solver. It may be used for:
# Setting analysis parameters
# Selecting working directory
# Running the Z88 solver

{{Version|1.2}}: The Z88 solver implementation has been completely refactored and this page has been updated accordingly.

==Installation== <!--T:10-->

<!--T:11-->
To use the Z88 solver, the open-source version of Z88 (Z88OS or Z88Adria) needs to be installed:
# Download the ZIP package with the code of either version:
#* Z88OS: [https://github.com/lscad/z88os official Z88OS repository] or [https://github.com/FreeCAD/Z88OS forked Z88OS repository]
#* Z88Adria: [https://en.z88.de/download-z88adria/ Z88Adria download page].
# Extract the ZIP contents to a folder of your choice.
# In the [[FEM_Preferences|FEM preferences]], go to the Z88 tab and set the path to the '''z88r''' binary. If you are on Windows, this would be the path to the file {{FileName|z88r.exe}} that is in the subfolder {{FileName|\bin\win64}} for Z88OS or {{FileName|\z88adria_windows}} for Z88Adria.

==Usage== <!--T:9-->

<!--T:3-->
# Create an [[Image:FEM_Analysis.svg|16px|link=FEM_Analysis]] [[FEM_Analysis|Analysis container]].
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select {{MenuCommand|Solve → [[Image:FEM_SolverZ88.svg|x16px]] Solver Z88}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|S}} then {{KEY|Z}}.
# Double-click the [[Image:FEM_SolverZ88.svg|x16px]] SolverZ88 object.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Analysis type}}.
# Press the {{Button|Write}} button.
# Press the {{Button|Run}} button.

<!--T:12-->
As a result you get an object called ''Z88_xxx_results'' (depending on the run simulation) in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]]. This is the same kind of result object one gets when running the [[FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools|CalculiX solver]]. Starting from this, you can visualize the results using [[FEM_PostPipelineFromResult|Post Pipeline]] and [[FEM_Workbench#Menu:_Results|Clip Filters]].

== Supported finite element types ==
The following types of finite elements are supported by the Z88 solver implementation:
* 2-node 3D truss,
* 8-node and 20-node hexahedron,
* 4-node nad 10-node tetrahedron,
* 6-node triangle and 8-node quadrangle - 3D shell and plate, 2D plane stress and axisymmetric formulations.
Linear triangles and quadrangles are not supported at all. Beam elements are not yet supported.

== Preferences == <!--T:13-->

<!--T:14-->
See the [[FEM_Preferences#Z88|Z88 preferences]] for the possible solver settings such as the used solver method.


